{
  "id": "22022421527",
  "title": "[ITD] Verify ITD and PkgC6 Interaction_emulation",
  "description": "<h4 id=\"isPasted\">Flow *</h4><ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 20px; margin: 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">Thermal telemetry information keeps flowing in PackageC6 state as well. Primecode uses this information and computes ITD correction voltage needed for the temperature compensation.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">Primecode shall not cause any wakes to apply ITD correction. There is a possibility that ITD updates to the Active WP arrive coincident with a PkgC wake event. In such a scenario, it is possible for RC to exit PkgC with a &quot;stale&quot; WP, but the RC will apply the updated Active WP after completing the Wake from PkgC.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">VCCIN retention voltage will always have worst case ITD voltage applied.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">DMR will utilize the Voltage Offset feature in the RC to apply ITD correction specific changes instead of creating new work point even for PkgC Flow. Legacy PkgC Entry workpoint consisted of applying worst case ITD compensation (0 or -40 based on SKU, fuse driven) .</li></ul><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-left: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; cursor: text; break-after: avoid; color: black; margin-top: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 1em; font-size: 18px; width: 778.513px; border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(204, 204, 204);\">Primecode Flow:</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">There is only one offset value that gets applied to all 3 work points in the RC. Since ITD is dependent on voltage and temperature, the base voltage for the workpoints must be adjusted so that a common offset can be applied.</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 20px; margin: 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">PrimeCode Calculates the worst case ITD compensation v/s active compensation for PkgC entry WP that way it does not need to keep track of the flavor of WP especially for PkgC flow.</li></ul><pre style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 15px 1em 15px 0px; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap; line-height: 19px; overflow: auto; background-color: inherit;\"><code style=\"box-sizing: border-box; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: 14.5px; font-family: &quot;Roboto Mono&quot;, Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&quot;, monospace, sans-serif; display: inline-block; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248); min-width: 50%; padding: 0.6em; border: 1px solid rgb(226, 226, 221); border-radius: 3px;\">#################################################################\n#Cal the worst case Idle voltage compensation v/s active delta\n#################################################################\n\n        #For GV Rails\n        IDLE_RATIO = MIN_RATIO (Pm)\n        IDLE_VOLTAGE = (VF-curve Voltage @ IDLE_RATIO)\n        #For fixed GV Rails\n        IDLE_RATIO = BOOT_RATIO\n        IDLE_VOLTAGE = BOOT_VOLTAGE\n\n        #ITD Math \n        ITD_COMPENSATION_WORST_CASE = ITD @ coldest temperature for PKGC_WP_IDLE_VOLTAGE_CFC_IO\n        ITD_COMPENSATION_ACTIVE_CASE = ITD @ post-boot temperature for PKGC_WP_IDLE_VOLTAGE_CFC_IO\n\n        DELTA_ITD = ITD_COMPENSATION_WORST_CASE - ITD_COMPENSATION_ACTIVE_CASE\n\n        PKGC_ENTRY_WP_VOLTAGE = IDLE_VOLTAGE + DELTA_ITD\n    </code></pre><ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 20px; margin: 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">The PkgC Entry WP voltage will have delta ITD compensation between worst case and boot active. The temperature when we are in PkgC state should be reflected in the ITD compensation being sent by the Primecode.</p></li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">The ITD correction at colder temperature is more accurate than assuming worst case resulting in achieving higher power savings PkgC states as well Auto States.</p></li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">The ITD compensation via Voffset feature can be disabled by writing 0 in the Voffset during PkgC Entry. But Primecode will need to convert the current Active WP into a PkgC Exit WP which accounts for ITD compensation in it.</p></li></ul></div><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-left: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; cursor: text; break-after: avoid; color: black; margin-top: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 1em; font-size: 18px; width: 778.513px; border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(204, 204, 204);\">PC6XITD Scenarios</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">The table below captures various scenarios with respect to the D2D and RC internal states for this cross product. * UCIe-PHY IP to respond to any ITD handshakes during L1 state * Auto completion logic in Vinfrastructure domain which addresses both Memory Fabric FIVR and the UCIE PHY FIVR for ITD handshakes * If the D2D IP is in the process of completing either of the flows and ITD or L1 exit request comes along they will be done in order received.</p><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-x: auto;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; text-align: left; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 100, 165);\"><b style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Scenarios across various flavors of PC6xITD</b> (<a href=\"https://docs.intel.com/documents/pm_doc/src/server/DMR/PM%20Features/Thermals/assets/DMR_Thermals.xlsx\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(65, 131, 196); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"-1\">source</a>)</p><table style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 15px 0px; font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); border-collapse: collapse; break-after: auto; line-height: 1.4;\"><tbody style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">ITD Request</th><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Current WP</th><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Entering PC6</th><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In PC6</th><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">UCIE Phy State</th><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">New Fix from UCIe (Auto ACK)</th><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Impact</th></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Active WP</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">No</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">L1 State</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Supported</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><br /></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Idle</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">N/A</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">L1 State</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Supported</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><br /></td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Exit WP</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">No</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">In the process of exiting L1.</p>(Retraining for PC6 Exit)</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Delay the ITD ACK by qualifying it with retraining complete</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">500ns normal ACK latency</p>if ITD occurs 6\u03bcs impact to the ACK - No Impact to PC6 Exit latency</td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; background-color: rgb(223, 235, 241); font-weight: bold; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">No</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; background-color: rgb(223, 235, 241); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Exit WP</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; background-color: rgb(223, 235, 241); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">No</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; background-color: rgb(223, 235, 241); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; background-color: rgb(223, 235, 241); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.3em 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">In the process of working the ITD flow( acked ITD on Idle WP)</p>Sees a L1 Exit request</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; background-color: rgb(223, 235, 241); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">UCIE PHY will exit L1 after voltage ramp.</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; background-color: rgb(223, 235, 241); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Impact to PC6 exit latency. But not new, it is not due to UCIE Phy fix because the RC can potentially also service ITD before exit WP.</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>1. Force Pkgc entry, disable wake events<p>2. Use itd.py do verify voltage values.</p><p>3. Change temperature and re-check voltage values.</p><h4>Configuration *</h4>Enable Pkgc and Cstates.<br /><br /><h4>Pass/Fail criteria *</h4>Offset voltage is not compromised while in Pkgc. Check that reflected voltage matches expectations with the aid of the content performing the calculation.<br /><br /><h4>Intent Verification Strategy *</h4>Simics.<br /><br /><h4>HW Requirements</h4>N/A<br /><br /><h4>SW Requirements</h4>Pcode, Acode, Patch23.<br /><br /><h4>Coverage</h4>N/A<br /><br /><h4>Component Interactions</h4>N/A",
